    "causal_summary": "This packet establishes a single canonical intake surface for spec-folder creation and repair, anchors /spec_kit:deep-research to a real spec.md, and hard-deletes deprecated middleware in favor of distributed governance. Canonical intake logic lives at .opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/references/intake-contract.md; /spec_kit:plan and /spec_kit:complete reference that module in place of inline duplication, and /spec_kit:plan --intake-only provides the standalone intake invocation path with an explicit YAML gate. /spec_kit:resume routes intake re-entry reasons to /spec_kit:plan --intake-only with prefilled state. /spec_kit:deep-research acquires an advisory lock during late INIT, classifies folder state, and writes back abridged findings through a machine-owned generated fence, per .opencode/skill/sk-deep-research/references/spec_check_protocol.md. The deprecated middleware wrappers (/spec_kit:handover, /spec_kit:debug, @handover, @speckit × 4 runtime mirrors each) are hard-deleted; @debug survives with Task-tool dispatch; a distributed-governance rule replaces the former @speckit exclusivity across CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, AGENTS_example_fs_enterprises.md, and system-spec-kit SKILL; /memory:save owns packet handover maintenance via handover_state routing; the :auto-debug flag is removed with explicit user escalation replacing it. Delivery spanned 15 milestones (M1-M9 delivered 2026-04-14, M10-M15 delivered 2026-04-15) including a 26-file downstream documentation sweep delegated to cli-copilot GPT-5.4 which completed 56 edits in one pass. A 10-iteration deep review flagged 12 findings (4 P0 / 4 P1 / 4 P2); five parallel Opus remediation agents fixed all 12 before closeout.",
